text: Azteca Uno (formerly: Azteca Trece) is a Mexican television network, owned by TV Azteca, it is found both via satellite and cable, it is the competent channel of the Televisa television network: Las Estrellas. Among its programming are the programs: Venga la alegría, Hechos and the competition program Exatlón México. == References == == Other websites == * Category:Television networks Category:Mexican culture Category:1960s establishments in Mexico
